I find most Australian movies suck not because they don't follow 'Mainstream Hollywood', but because the dialogue is unbelievable and clunky and besides Paul Hogan, I'm not sure if there has ever been an 'Australian Hero', most of them in the movies just cower and hide until the killer eventually finds and kills them.  Furthermore, I understand that The Outback is in Australia, but it's a very depressing backdrop, and those movies just keep panning it like it's the Swiss Alps or a South American Rain Forest.  Lastly, the mannerisms in the actors in Australian movies remind me of a live action 'Wallace & Gromit' impression.  I appreciate dry humor, but when the humor is so dry that the joke is that they never made one, well, that's not comedy.
He actually started out on Home & Away and then eventually landed the role on True Blood :) Aussie humour isnt for everyone lol Good Movie!

Candy. Chopper. The Castle. Gettin Square. Dirty Deeds. Dogs in Space. Romper Stomper. The Proposition. Mad max (1&2). Kenny. Two Hands. Animal Kingdom. 10 Canoes. I love you too, and Little fish.
